    "narrative": "The Zurich Zebras enter today\u2019s slate with **Pete Crow-Armstrong** serving as our anchor, boasting the highest efficiency rating of the day at 75.88. His matchup against Ryne Nelson is the definition of an optimal setup; the combination of a favorable right-handed platoon advantage and a base projection bolstered by consistent high-end production makes him a must-start. Joining him in the elite tier is **Colt Keith** (65.83), who benefits significantly from an advantageous matchup against Jack Leiter and a productive spot in the #3 hole. Both players are expected to anchor our Roto categories today, with **Caleb Durbin** (65.14) also projecting as a high-floor play despite his #9 batting order slot, as he draws a exploitable matchup against Hunter Brown and benefits from favorable wind conditions that enhance his efficiency profile.\n\nWhile we are aggressive in seeking stolen bases, we must navigate a few high-risk matchups. **Yordan Alvarez** (53.69) faces a tough challenge against Early, where a stagnant SP skill rating and a stiff L/L platoon disadvantage suppress his ceiling compared to his standard output. We have relegated **Chase Meidroth** (44.21) to the bench; while he remained the closest candidate for inclusion, the lack of defensive premium and a neutral matchup against Michael King meant he could not crack our high-efficiency threshold. We are monitoring **Carson Benge** closely, as the \"Lineup Pending\" status and a negative L/L platoon split against Reid Detmers keep him sidelined for now. With **Zac Veen** still in the minors and **Christian Yelich** remaining on the IL, we will continue to rely on the depth of our outfield corps\u2014including the platoon-boosted **Josh Smith**\u2014to mitigate the sting of those absences.",
